Method Reference:
    - simplified (short-cut) to lambda expressions (java 8)
    - compact & easy form of lambda expressions

Types of method reference:
1. Reference to a static method
   - class/interfaceName::methodName
   - ParseNumbersClass p = number -> Integer.parseInt(number); is same as Integer::parseInt;

2. Reference to an instance (non-static) method for a particular object
- particular-obj (Student s = new Student();) -> particular type
   - object-name::methodName
   - student::showDetails, etc

3. Reference to an instance (non-static) method for a arbitrary object
- arbitrary-obj: (List<Students> ls = new ArrayList<>();) -> any type within specified type
    - object-name::methodName
    - Arrays::equals, Integer::parseInt, etc

4. Reference to a constructor
   - ClassName::new

